  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">James Miller M&apos;Kim purchased for Maria Weston Chapman a copy of the Episcopal Prayer Book, published by Lippincott &amp; Grambo, &quot;containing as a frontispiece Schaeffer&apos;s [sic] picture of Christus Consolator&quot; with the black man in chains left out. M&apos;Kim intends to accompany the book with a letter giving a more detailed account of this &quot;new illustration of American pro-slavery diablerie and northern commercial crudeness.&quot; M&apos;Kim will also send Maria W. Chapman a Bible illustrated with the same frontispiece and trusts that she will send the latter to Ary Scheffer, &quot;whom you very well know.&quot;</subfield>
